4:47 PM

Core Terms:
Term	Definition
Chat/Session/Conversation	Entire exchange from start to end
Turn	One user message + one assistant response
Message	Single block of text from user or assistant
Response/Reply	Assistant's single output to a user message
Prompt	Input text given to the model
System Prompt	Hidden instructions defining assistant behavior
User Prompt	Your message/question
Context Window	Total tokens the model can see (includes system prompt, chat history, current message)
Token	Unit of text (~4 characters or ~¾ word in English)

Prompt Engineering Terms:
Term	Definition
Few-shot	Providing examples in the prompt to guide output format
Zero-shot	No examples, just instructions
Chain-of-thought	Asking model to reason step-by-step
Role prompting	"You are a [expert]..." framing
Instruction	Direct command ("List 5 items")
Constraint	Limitation ("Under 100 words")
Persona	Defined character/voice for responses

Claude-Specific:
Term	Definition
Memory	Persistent user preferences across chats
Artifact	Rendered output (code, documents, visualizations)
Tool call	Model invoking external function (bash, search, etc.)
Context compaction	Summarizing old messages when context fills


Claude is AI and can make mistakes. Please double-check responses.
